Description: Five fragments of dark brown human hair (?) string used as binding. The string consists of 3 's'-spun elements, 'z'-plied. One fragment has a knot. The knotted fragment appears to be at least two pieces of string. The smallst fragment, fragment five, has mud/human remains attached. The fragments three and four are kinked.
Dimensions: Length: 270 millimetres (Long section including short tail - Main Fragment (knotted))
Bibliographic references: Adams et al 1999 / Kulubnarti III: The Cemeteries (p. 63)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Dr William Yewdale Adams
Donated by: W S Webb Museum of Anthropology (University of Kentucky)
Additional IDs: Excavation/small finds number: 93.2.55B (excavation object cat. no.)
